                                                                                                                                  Business Briefs

               
	 Mumbai, Jan. 15: Market regulator Sebi today asked the BSE and the NSE to formulate volatility indices to be used by investors for derivative trading. Exchanges shall construct a volatility index and disseminate the same, the regulator said in a communication to the bourses. The exchanges will be free to adopt the globally available volatility index or develop their own index, Sebi said. 
              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 15: NTPCs joint venture with Bhel will start offering engineering, procurement and construction services to projects in the next three to four months. 
              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 15: Essar Energy Overseas, a subsidiary of Essar Oil, has acquired a 50 per cent stake in Kenya Petroleum Refineries, a 4-million-tonne per annum refinery in Mombassa, Kenya for an undisclosed amount. 
              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 15: Shishir Bajaj, younger brother of Bajaj Auto chairman Rahul, today said the family patriarch tried to oust him from the chair of a group holding company during a proceeding before the Company Law Board. 
              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 15: Shubhashis Gangopadhyay today took over as the new adviser to finance minister P. Chidambaram, replacing Parthasarathi Shome who resigned last month.
                                                            
